+# Solution for Issue #38321
+
+## Root Cause
+
+`SqlServerQueryableMethodTranslatingExpressionVisitor.TransformJsonQueryToTable` looked up the
+container column (the JSON column whose type mapping drives OPENJSON generation) exclusively via
+`IEntityType.GetTableMappings()`. When the entity is mapped to a **view** (`.ToView(...)`) instead
+of a table, `GetTableMappings()` returns an empty sequence. The subsequent `.Single(c => c is not
+null)` call then throws `InvalidOperationException: Sequence contains no elements`.
+
+The regression was introduced when the code was changed to look up the container column from the
+relational model rather than directly from the property. View mappings were not included in the
+lookup.
+
+## Change
+
+**File:** `src/EFCore.SqlServer/Query/Internal/SqlServerQueryableMethodTranslatingExpressionVisitor.cs`
+
+In `TransformJsonQueryToTable`, the line that finds the container column now concatenates both
+table mappings and view mappings (cast to the common `ITableMappingBase` interface) before
+searching for the column:
+
+```csharp
+// Before (fails for view-mapped entities)
+var containerColumn = structuralType.ContainingEntityType.GetTableMappings()
+    .Select(m => m.Table.FindColumn(containerColumnName))
+    .Single(c => c is not null)!;
+
+// After (handles tables and views)
+var containingEntityType = structuralType.ContainingEntityType;
+var containerColumn = containingEntityType.GetTableMappings().Cast<ITableMappingBase>()
+    .Concat(containingEntityType.GetViewMappings())
+    .Select(m => m.Table.FindColumn(containerColumnName))
+    .Single(c => c is not null)!;
+```
+
+Both `ITableMapping` and `IViewMapping` extend `ITableMappingBase`, which exposes `ITableBase
+Table` and `ITableBase.FindColumn(string)`. This means the column lookup works correctly for
+both tables and views through the same interface.
+
+## Files Edited
+
+- `src/EFCore.SqlServer/Query/Internal/SqlServerQueryableMethodTranslatingExpressionVisitor.cs`
